commutate

commutate.Rd

...

commutate(algo_0, algo_1, ...)

Arguments

algo_0

A component algorithm to be commutated to when e == 0 (algo_base)
algo_1

A component algorithm to be commutated to when e == 1 (algo_base)
...

For future usage

Value

A component algorithm whose inner logic commutates algo_0 and algo_1 based on e

Examples

# Switch two simple algos:
require(haricot);
algo_0 <- algo_01$new();
#> INFO [2018-09-02 19:49:02] set_dim_i: increase input dimension by 1
#> INFO [2018-09-02 19:49:02] set_dim_o: increase output dimension by 1
#> Error in set_graph_edge(self, source_algo, source_bit, target_algo, target_bit,     ...): argument "source_algo" is missing, with no default
algo_0$plot();
#> Error in eval(expr, envir, enclos): attempt to apply non-function
algo_1 <- algo_10$new();
#> INFO [2018-09-02 19:49:02] set_dim_i: increase input dimension by 1
#> INFO [2018-09-02 19:49:02] set_dim_o: increase output dimension by 1
algo_1$plot();
commutated <- commutate(algo_0, algo_1);
#> Error in commutate(algo_0, algo_1): algo_0 does not implement algo_base
commutated$exec("00");
#> Error in eval(expr, envir, enclos): object 'commutated' not found
commutated$exec("10");
#> Error in eval(expr, envir, enclos): object 'commutated' not found
commutated$exec("01");
#> Error in eval(expr, envir, enclos): object 'commutated' not found
commutated$exec("11");
#> Error in eval(expr, envir, enclos): object 'commutated' not found
commutated$plot();
#> Error in eval(expr, envir, enclos): object 'commutated' not found
